# 🔍 Production Readiness Audit — Revelton TB Extension Dashboard

> **Auditor perspective**: Senior Full-Stack Developer + IoT Engineer  
> **Audit date**: 2026-07-09  
> **Scope**: Complete codebase under `revelton-tb-extension-dashboard/`  
> **Files reviewed**: 15+ TypeScript files (~6,500 lines), templates, SCSS

---

## Executive Summary

| Area | Rating | Notes |
|------|--------|-------|
| Architecture | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ | Solid layered design (core/features/shared) |
| Type Safety | ⭐⭐ | Heavy `any` usage undermines TypeScript benefits |
| Memory Management | ⭐⭐⭐ | Most intervals cleared, but subscription leaks present |
| Security | ⭐⭐ | DEBUG flag left on, no input sanitization on RPC calls |
| Error Handling | ⭐⭐⭐ | Basic error handling exists, but inconsistent |
| Performance | ⭐⭐⭐ | Debouncing present, but excessive HTTP calls on discovery |
| Test Coverage | ⭐ | No tests found |
| Production Config | ⭐⭐ | Mock data, hardcoded values, debug logging |
| IoT Best Practices | ⭐⭐⭐ | Good device discovery, weak offline/resilience handling |

**Overall verdict**: 🟡 **Not production-ready** — 8 critical issues and 14 major issues must be addressed before deployment.

---

## 🔴 CRITICAL Issues (Must fix before production)

### C1. DEBUG flag is `true` in production service

**File**: [hotel-state.service.ts](file:///home/nurlansarkhanov/Desktop/code/Revelton/thingsboard-extention/src/app/components/revelton-tb-extension-dashboard/core/services/hotel-state.service.ts#L9)

```typescript
const DEBUG = true; // TEMPORARY: enable to debug Mews Bridge data flow
```

This floods the browser console with hundreds of log messages per second across 1,792-line file. Every `log()` call (50+ occurrences) triggers. In production this will:
- Degrade performance (console serialization is expensive)
- Expose internal architecture to anyone with dev tools open
- Fill up browser memory over time

> [!CAUTION]
> **Fix**: Set `const DEBUG = false;` immediately. Better: use an environment variable or ThingsBoard widget setting.

---

### C2. Mock guest count in production statistics

**File**: [hotel-state.service.ts](file:///home/nurlansarkhanov/Desktop/code/Revelton/thingsboard-extention/src/app/components/revelton-tb-extension-dashboard/core/services/hotel-state.service.ts#L815-L819)

```typescript
// Mock guest count: 1 for odd rooms, 2 for even rooms
const rn = parseInt(room.roomData.sensorData.roomNumber?.toString() || "1");
inHouseGuests += rn % 2 === 0 ? 2 : 1;
```

The "In-House Guests" KPI displayed on the hotel dashboard is **entirely fake**. This is production-visible data that hotel staff will rely on for operational decisions.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Fix**: Either source actual guest count from MEWS API, or remove the metric entirely. Displaying fake data to hotel staff is worse than showing `N/A`.

