### C4. No input validation on RPC commands

**File**: [room-detail-panel.component.ts](file:///home/nurlansarkhanov/Desktop/code/Revelton/thingsboard-extention/src/app/components/revelton-tb-extension-dashboard/features/room-view/room-detail-panel.component.ts#L1249-L1281)

```typescript
private saveAttribute(trv: any, key: string, value: any): void {
  // No validation of key or value
  ctx.http.post(`/api/plugins/telemetry/DEVICE/${deviceId}/SHARED_SCOPE`, { [key]: value }).subscribe(...)
  ctx.http.post(`/api/rpc/oneway/${deviceId}`, { method: methods[key], params: value }).subscribe();
}
```

The `saveAttribute` method sends arbitrary values directly to ThingsBoard without validation:
- Temperature setpoint has no bounds checking (user could send `999°C` or `-50°C`)
- System mode has no whitelist validation
- No rate limiting on RPC calls (rapid UI clicks → rapid device commands)

> [!CAUTION]
> **Fix**: Add validation: `if (key === 'current_heating_setpoint') { value = Math.max(5, Math.min(35, value)); }`. Whitelist modes to `['auto', 'heat', 'off']`. Add RPC debouncing.

---

### C5. Hardcoded timezone (`Europe/Prague`) across 5+ files

**Files**: [hotel-state.service.ts](file:///home/nurlansarkhanov/Desktop/code/Revelton/thingsboard-extention/src/app/components/revelton-tb-extension-dashboard/core/services/hotel-state.service.ts#L476), [revelton-hotel.component.ts](file:///home/nurlansarkhanov/Desktop/code/Revelton/thingsboard-extention/src/app/components/revelton-tb-extension-dashboard/features/hotel-dashboard/revelton-hotel.component.ts#L511), [room-detail-panel.component.ts](file:///home/nurlansarkhanov/Desktop/code/Revelton/thingsboard-extention/src/app/components/revelton-tb-extension-dashboard/features/room-view/room-detail-panel.component.ts#L1191), [room-data.service.ts](file:///home/nurlansarkhanov/Desktop/code/Revelton/thingsboard-extention/src/app/components/revelton-tb-extension-dashboard/core/services/room-data.service.ts#L744)

`'Europe/Prague'` appears as a string literal in **4 separate files**. If this dashboard is deployed at any other hotel (even within Europe), all timestamps, check-in/check-out times, and weather data will be wrong.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Fix**: Extract to a single `HOTEL_TIMEZONE` constant in a config file, or read from ThingsBoard widget settings.

